cs.NI, cs.DB, cs.CR, cs.SI, cs.CY

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on monitoring and troubleshooting mobile broadband networks. 
- cs.DB (Databases) is also likely as the paper presents a data mining toolkit for analyzing mobile broadband data. 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is a possibility as the paper mentions the critical purposes for which mobile broadband networks are used, which may include security-sensitive applications. 
- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is a possibility as the paper mentions crowdsourced monitoring methods. 
- cs.CY (Computers and Society) is a possibility as the paper mentions healthcare as one of the critical purposes for which mobile broadband networks are used.
